EpiphanyAgent Repository License Notice
=======================================

This repository is a multi-license distribution. Different parts of the
repository are available under different terms.

Nothing in this file narrows, revokes, or relabels rights already granted by
upstream licenses. In particular, nothing in this file should be read as
withdrawing any permission granted by Apache License 2.0 for Apache-covered
material.

1. Scope
--------

For this file:

- `Project-Authored Material` means original software, documentation, and other
  repository content authored for EpiphanyAgent, except where a file or
  directory states different terms.
- `Upstream Material` means material copied or adapted from third parties and
  distributed under their own licenses.
- `Mixed Apache Files` means files under `vendor/codex/**` that contain
  project-authored changes on top of upstream Apache-licensed material.

2. Upstream And Third-Party Material
------------------------------------

- All material under `vendor/codex/**` remains subject to its upstream licenses
  and notices, including Apache License 2.0 at `vendor/codex/LICENSE` and any
  applicable `NOTICE` or file-level notices.
- Other third-party material distributed with the repository keeps its own
  license terms where provided.
- You must continue to comply with those upstream terms when using,
  redistributing, or modifying upstream material.

3. Public License For Project-Authored Material
-----------------------------------------------

Except where a file or directory says otherwise, Project-Authored Material
outside `vendor/codex/**` is licensed to the public under:

- PolyForm Noncommercial License 1.0.0

The full text of that license appears in Appendix A of this file.

Required Notice: Copyright 2026 EpiphanyAgent authors and contributors.

4. Commercial License Option
----------------------------

If you want to use Project-Authored Material for any purpose not permitted by
PolyForm Noncommercial License 1.0.0, you must obtain a separate written
commercial license from the applicable copyright holder or another party
expressly authorized in writing to grant that license.

Commercial rights are not granted by:

- source availability
- public access to this repository
- silence
- estoppel by implication
- the fact that the licensors are not yet organized as a corporation or LLC

A natural person can own and license copyright. Until a separate business
entity is formed and designated in writing, any commercial license for
Project-Authored Material may be offered directly by the individual copyright
holder or holders.

5. Mixed Apache Files Under `vendor/codex/**`
---------------------------------------------

Some files under `vendor/codex/**` contain project-authored changes layered on
top of upstream Apache-licensed code.

For those files:

- Apache License 2.0 and the applicable upstream notices still apply.
- You must not read this repository notice as converting those files into a
  PolyForm-only codebase.
- To the extent the project owns copyright in new additions to those files, the
  project may also offer separate commercial terms for its own contributions.
- This repository notice does not claim to erase or retract Apache-2.0
  permissions already granted for Apache-covered material.

The strongest commercial boundary in this repository therefore applies to
clearly separable Project-Authored Material outside `vendor/codex/**`,
including `epiphany-core/**` and other non-vendored project files.

6. Open Source Status
---------------------

Because the public license path for Project-Authored Material is PolyForm
Noncommercial License 1.0.0 rather than an OSI-approved license, the
repository as a whole is source-available and dual-licensed. It is not an OSI
Open Source distribution as a whole.

7. Reference Structures
-----------------------

This licensing structure intentionally borrows the general dual-license shape
used by established projects such as Qt and MySQL:

- one public-facing license path
- one separate commercial license path

This repository does not claim that Qt or MySQL use the same exact public
license terms used here. Those projects are referenced only as structural
examples of dual licensing, not as the operative terms of this repository.

8. Contributions
----------------

External contributions are accepted only under the EpiphanyAgent Contributor
License Agreement in `CONTRIBUTOR_LICENSE_AGREEMENT.md`, or under a separate
written agreement accepted by the Project Steward.

The contributor agreement is intentionally broad. Contributors keep ownership
of their contributions, but grant the Project Steward the right to sublicense
and relicense those contributions under any license or terms the Project
Steward chooses, including commercial or proprietary terms.

The project should not accept non-trivial outside contributions unless the
contributor has agreed to that contributor agreement or an equivalent written
agreement.

